cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and language understanding. The use of cognitive language processing signals such as gaze and EEG features also suggests a potential fit for the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also involves the use of machine learning models, indicating a possible fit for the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper explores the potential of using human language processing data for NLP, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
